{"type":"message","id":"40697c56","parentId":"ef0bc920","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:37:57.066Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_7z1f58wl4pn0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 003313\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine the best next action based on the goals and insights documented.\r\n\r\nKey insights from this session:\r\n1. Compression-Causal Duality hypothesis - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n2. TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next action\r\n3. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step seems to be implementing the TIC classifier experiment. I should look at the existing pulse logs and implement the classification system.\r\n\r\nLet me first check what pulse logs exist and then implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nSince I'm stateless and need to make a specific file edit, I should:\r\n1. Create or modify a file related to the TIC experiment\r\n2. Make it concrete and actionable\r\n\r\nThe most logical action would be to start implementing the TIC experiment framework - perhaps creating a script or document that outlines the implementation.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n4. Measures accuracy against success criteria\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to build a classifier that can identify invariant/variant patterns across pulse logs and measure prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic_experiment.ps1` - a PowerShell script that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier on recent pulse logs, measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction performance against the success criteria (>70%, >60%).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Validates: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Config\r\n$LOG_DIR = \"logs\"\r\n$MIN_INVARIANT_RATIO = 0.5  # λ threshold for invariant classification\r\n$TARGET_INVARIANT_ACC = 0.70\r\n$TARGET_PREDICTION_ACC = 0.60\r\n\r\n# Find recent pulse logs\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem \"$LOG_DIR/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseLogs.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Experiment starting with $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Track metrics\r\n$invariantCorrect = 0\r\n$variantCorrect = 0\r\n$predictionCorrect = 0\r\n$totalComparisons = 0\r\n\r\n# Compare consecutive pulses for invariance detection\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulseLogs.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $current = Get-Content $pulseLogs[$i].FullName -Raw\r\n    $next = Get-Content $pulseLogs[$i + 1].FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Simple invariant detection: shared structure markers\r\n    # Goal lines, heading patterns, section headers = invariant\r\n    # Specific values, timestamps, content = variant\r\n    \r\n    $currentInvariantMarkers = @()\r\n    $currentVariantMarkers = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references (invariant)\r\n    if ($current -match '## Goals|## Pending|## Completed') {\r\n        $currentInvariantMarkers += \"structure\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract timestamp/content differences (variant)\r\n    if ($current -match '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}' -and $next -match '\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}') {\r\n        $currentVariantMarkers += \"temporal\"\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Prediction: extract key invariant from current to predict next\r\n    # If goals section is stable, predict stability\r\n    $goalsStable = ($current -match '## Goals') -and ($next -match '## Goals')\r\n    \r\n    # Score\r\n    $invariantScore = $currentInvariantMarkers.Count / \r\n        ($currentInvariantMarkers.Count + $currentVariantMarkers.Count + 1)\r\n    \r\n    if ($invariantScore -ge $MIN_INVARIANT_RATIO) {\r\n        # Classified as invariant - check if goals structure persists\r\n        if ($goalsStable) { $invariantCorrect++ }\r\n    } else {\r\n        # Classified as variant - check if content changed\r\n        if (-not $goalsStable) { $variantCorrect++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Next-pulse prediction: if invariant structure exists, predict stability\r\n    if ($goalsStable -and ($current -match 'Phase|##')) {\r\n        $predictionCorrect++\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $totalComparisons++\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate metrics\r\n$classificationAcc = ($invariantCorrect + $variantCorrect) / ($totalComparisons * 2)\r\n$predictionAcc = $predictionCorrect / $totalComparisons\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC RESULTS ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Classification Accuracy: $([math]::Round($classificationAcc * 100, 1))% (target: $([math]::Round($TARGET_INVARIANT_ACC * 100))%)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Prediction Accuracy: $([math]::Round($predictionAcc * 100, 1))% (target: $([math]::Round($TARGET\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:33:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774327077064}}
